Others: The ICC Men’s T20 World Cup 2022 title clash between Pakistan and England is going to take place on 13 November.
Umpires Marais Erasmus and Kumar Dharmasena will be on-field duties.
TV umpire will be Chris Gaffaney and the fourth umpire will be Paul Reiffel.
England thrashed India by 10 wickets on Thursday.
Buttler hit 80 runs and Hales hit 86 runs for England.
Pakistan reached the Men’s T20 World Cup final after defeating New Zealand by seven wickets on Wednesday.
Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan smashed key half-centuries for Pakistan.
The ICC T20 World Cup final will be played between Pakistan and England on 13 November 2022.
